  "summary": "Important: libtiff security update",
  "details": "The libtiff packages contain a library of functions for manipulating Tagged Image File Format (TIFF) files.  \n\nSecurity Fix(es):  \n\n  * libtiff: libtiff: Arbitrary code execution or denial of service via signed integer overflow in TIFF file processing (CVE-2026-4775)\n\n\nFor more details about the security issue(s), including the impact, a CVSS score, acknowledgments, and other related information, refer to the CVE page(s) listed in the References section.\n",
